WEBVTT

00:00:17.150 --> 00:00:20.060
Where... am I?

00:00:26.580 --> 00:00:27.959
I'm sorry! I'll leave an offering!

00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:28.790
Please, just spare me!

00:00:28.791 --> 00:00:31.620
Wait, I'm not dead yet.

00:00:37.630 --> 00:00:38.630
Sara senpai?

00:00:40.410 --> 00:00:41.880
You're as unreliable as ever.

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:47.000
I thought you were...

00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:49.240
A monster?

00:00:49.241 --> 00:00:52.060
Don't! You'll summon
it if you say it out loud!

00:00:52.130 --> 00:00:53.230
No, I won't.

00:00:53.290 --> 00:00:53.740
I'm...

00:00:53.741 --> 00:00:56.060
Stop, please don't say it!

00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:57.910
I...

00:01:01.330 --> 00:01:02.330
Found it.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.260
I'm finally pulling my weight for once.

00:01:05.780 --> 00:01:07.600
And you escaped the
"sleeping bag" fate, too.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:10.440
This is the last number...

00:01:13.007 --> 00:01:14.497
I twisted my ankle.

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:24.080
Guess you're still a burden after all.

00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:30.730
Get on.

00:01:33.702 --> 00:01:35.042
You're... carrying me?

00:01:36.530 --> 00:01:37.530
I can't.

00:01:38.430 --> 00:01:40.100
Then I'll just have to make you.

00:01:41.260 --> 00:01:42.550
This doesn't feel right...

00:01:43.773 --> 00:01:45.683
Would you rather be caught by a monster?

00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:48.220
Hurry up.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:19.300
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Special Episode 2)

00:03:04.310 --> 00:03:05.580
What's this?

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:06.980
What is all this?

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.150
- We don't need this.
- Put it over there.

00:03:13.070 --> 00:03:15.850
- Put it right here in the middle.
- Man, I'm beat.

00:03:24.050 --> 00:03:25.480
How did you manage that?

00:03:27.630 --> 00:03:29.300
- I tripped.
- I don't mean the ankle.

00:03:29.430 --> 00:03:31.510
I mean Sara carrying you back.

00:03:32.570 --> 00:03:33.490
It's because I fell.

00:03:33.491 --> 00:03:34.919
He was just being kind enough to carry me.

00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:36.060
That's exactly the point.

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:38.550
Since when does Sara do stuff like that?

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.820
He did it when Taiga senpai broke his leg.

00:03:42.730 --> 00:03:44.390
That was years ago.

00:03:45.530 --> 00:03:47.140
Sara senpai has always been gentle.

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:50.730
You're the only one
who'd ever call him "gentle."

00:03:52.050 --> 00:03:53.270
Stop gossiping.

00:03:53.990 --> 00:03:54.990
Come and help.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:57.060
That's not my job.

00:03:58.200 --> 00:04:00.710
It's not exactly a Vice
President's job either.

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:03.510
You're basically a Vice
President in name only, right?

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:06.330
You just modeled for that one poster.

00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:09.260
And now all you do is complain.

00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:11.240
And what have you done?

00:04:14.470 --> 00:04:16.270
You've just been sitting
there doing nothing.

00:04:17.630 --> 00:04:20.320
Dumping everything
on Jin... you're useless.

00:04:24.140 --> 00:04:25.980
If you're not going to help, I'm leaving.

00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:28.520
You're leaving?

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:30.330
You might want to rethink that.

00:04:31.870 --> 00:04:33.760
I've got the car keys.

00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:37.521
If I call a cab,
it'll probably be here in two hours.

00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:42.420
Damn it.

00:04:44.230 --> 00:04:45.980
What do people even see in a guy like that?

00:05:18.270 --> 00:05:19.490
Don't look so down.

00:05:23.200 --> 00:05:24.510
I just feel so bad...

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:27.500
about being so useless.

00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:31.680
I just wanted to be helpful.

00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:35.750
But you were.

00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:39.280
How?

00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:41.890
You brought me all those supplies.

00:05:45.960 --> 00:05:47.060
Thanks.

00:06:07.300 --> 00:06:08.600
I can finally see your face now.

00:06:10.260 --> 00:06:11.260
Fuu.

00:06:21.350 --> 00:06:22.519
Crap, it's gonna burn!

00:06:22.520 --> 00:06:23.400
If it burns, you're eating it.

00:06:23.401 --> 00:06:24.800
No way!

00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:26.480
Hey, eat up, eat up!

00:06:37.910 --> 00:06:38.910
Fuu... are you okay?

00:06:45.990 --> 00:06:47.680
Sara senpai is so mean.

00:06:50.540 --> 00:06:52.720
Wasn't he being nice to you?

00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:58.370
My head is just... all over the place.

00:06:59.590 --> 00:07:01.140
Aren't you always like that?

00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:04.000
It's worse than usual.

00:07:06.550 --> 00:07:07.750
It's all his fault.

00:07:09.890 --> 00:07:10.890
He's so mean.

00:07:11.600 --> 00:07:14.990
- Who wants the burnt ones?
- Hey, you overcooked these!

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:17.000
- What are you guys doing?
- Ah...

00:07:17.170 --> 00:07:20.939
- I really want to hear Sara senpai sing.
- Oh! Me too, me too!

00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:23.030
- Come on, Sara senpai, just one song!
- Yeah, please!

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:24.310
Please, we're begging you!

00:07:24.850 --> 00:07:27.120
- Just one, please!
- Pretty please!

00:07:27.760 --> 00:07:34.590
Sara senpai! Sara senpai! Sara senpai!

00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:36.640
Sara senpai! Sara senpai!

00:07:39.340 --> 00:07:40.340
Fine, I get it.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.600
If I sing, will you all finally shut up?

00:08:01.410 --> 00:08:02.610
What do you want to hear?

00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:11.710
Go on, pick a song.

00:08:17.170 --> 00:08:18.420
Fuu's favorite.

00:08:20.430 --> 00:08:21.430
Got it.

00:08:51.130 --> 00:08:55.220
♪ In a sudden downpour ♪

00:08:56.710 --> 00:09:03.520
♪ If an umbrella falls at your feet ♪

00:09:04.030 --> 00:09:07.860
♪ Please, hold it over yourself ♪

00:09:09.570 --> 00:09:15.489
♪ And head home before you catch a cold ♪

00:09:15.490 --> 00:09:23.110
♪ Even if I can't be
there to wipe your tears ♪

00:09:23.590 --> 00:09:29.300
♪ I'll send a letter with these flowers ♪

00:09:30.620 --> 00:09:36.250
♪ You found me when I
was nowhere to be found ♪

00:09:36.350 --> 00:09:42.760
♪ So I'll just keep on praying ♪

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:46.479
♪ That only happiness
finds its way to you ♪

00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:50.240
♪ I'll just keep on praying ♪

00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:58.560
♪ That tomorrow, my
love will still be there ♪

00:10:16.640 --> 00:10:17.880
What should I do, Fuu...

00:10:20.510 --> 00:10:21.710
What on earth should I do...

00:10:57.670 --> 00:10:59.150
How am I supposed to handle this...

00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:03.590
What do I do...

00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:07.680
Ah...

00:11:11.900 --> 00:11:13.190
I just wanted you to notice me.

00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:16.620
Hey, don't blame me.

00:11:19.420 --> 00:11:20.620
It's the truth, isn't it?

00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:38.530
So...

00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:47.240
What should I do?

00:11:52.380 --> 00:11:53.850
Those two are dating.

00:11:54.760 --> 00:11:56.080
They've been together for a year.

00:11:58.440 --> 00:11:59.540
I didn't know.

00:12:01.470 --> 00:12:02.570
Well, now you do.

00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:04.680
Let's go.

00:12:19.460 --> 00:12:20.860
Are you really that shocked?

00:12:23.030 --> 00:12:24.030
It's just...

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:25.720
I never imagined they were together.

00:12:26.760 --> 00:12:28.470
Are you shocked that they're dating?

00:12:32.850 --> 00:12:34.050
Or was it the kiss?

00:12:45.010 --> 00:12:46.210
Let me ask you something.

00:12:50.140 --> 00:12:51.340
What?

00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:54.120
Look at me when I'm talking to you.

00:12:57.610 --> 00:12:58.810
I can still talk...

00:12:59.460 --> 00:13:00.700
even if I'm not looking at you.

00:13:01.920 --> 00:13:03.590
Look up at me.

00:13:13.700 --> 00:13:14.800
Do you like me?

00:13:18.140 --> 00:13:19.240
Don't look away.

00:13:19.590 --> 00:13:20.820
Look me in the eye.

00:13:32.490 --> 00:13:33.490
Well?

00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:35.810
Do you have feelings for me?

00:13:41.940 --> 00:13:42.940
Yes...

00:13:46.030 --> 00:13:47.130
What was that?

00:13:47.990 --> 00:13:49.090
I can't hear you.

00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:53.170
I like you, Sara senpai.

00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:55.550
I like you a lot.

00:13:56.210 --> 00:13:57.940
I've liked you for years.

00:14:05.240 --> 00:14:06.480
I'm still not quite getting it.

00:14:09.440 --> 00:14:10.720
Make it a little clearer for me.

00:14:59.160 --> 00:15:00.160
Fuu.

00:15:02.310 --> 00:15:03.510
What's wrong?

00:15:06.210 --> 00:15:07.410
Did you have a nightmare?

00:15:11.530 --> 00:15:12.530
Fuu?

00:15:28.490 --> 00:15:29.490
I'm not shy.

00:15:42.040 --> 00:15:43.040
Of course not.

00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:44.930
We've been dating for months now.

00:15:46.780 --> 00:15:48.849
Why would my heart be racing like this?

00:15:48.850 --> 00:15:49.890
Wait, Fuu.

00:15:50.290 --> 00:15:51.330
What is going on with you?

00:15:54.170 --> 00:15:55.370
Sara senpai.

00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:58.320
I dreamed about my parallel self.

00:16:04.020 --> 00:16:05.530
In that other world,

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:07.720
you and I were together.

00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:12.300
That Sara senpai had a sharp tongue,
but he was gentle...

00:16:13.060 --> 00:16:14.860
Just like the person
you swapped bodies with.

00:16:17.430 --> 00:16:19.500
And that Fuu was so shy.

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:22.690
We went camping together.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:26.480
The place looked just like
this. It was pure déjà vu.

00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:30.360
You said it before, right?

00:16:30.820 --> 00:16:32.900
That no matter the world,
there are common threads.

00:16:34.890 --> 00:16:36.700
Do you think the parallel Fuu and Sara

00:16:37.400 --> 00:16:39.280
come and stay here sometimes, too?

00:16:42.800 --> 00:16:44.000
Who knows.

00:16:45.060 --> 00:16:46.079
Ever since that accident,

00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:47.830
I haven't dreamed of that white room again.

00:16:48.890 --> 00:16:50.060
Then why did I...?

00:16:52.370 --> 00:16:54.130
Could I be traveling
to parallel worlds now?

00:16:55.990 --> 00:16:57.090
I won't let you go.

00:16:58.860 --> 00:17:00.420
Did he do anything to you in the dream?

00:17:01.340 --> 00:17:02.440
What do you mean?

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:04.850
Like, did he touch you?

00:17:05.600 --> 00:17:07.000
Or did he do something even worse?

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:10.180
Are you jealous?

00:17:10.860 --> 00:17:12.210
Of yourself in a parallel world?

00:17:13.350 --> 00:17:14.620
What if I am?

00:17:15.870 --> 00:17:18.230
Honestly, you're such a jealous mess.

00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:21.550
Are you going to tell me or not?

00:17:21.880 --> 00:17:23.300
I'm telling you right now.

00:17:24.040 --> 00:17:25.620
That's not what I meant.

00:17:26.330 --> 00:17:27.730
In the dream,

00:17:27.870 --> 00:17:30.010
were you just watching us as a bystander?

00:17:30.460 --> 00:17:31.560
Or did you

00:17:31.780 --> 00:17:33.740
actually become that
world's version of yourself?

00:17:35.630 --> 00:17:36.730
What if you...

00:17:37.660 --> 00:17:39.940
were inside that Fuu's body?

00:17:41.660 --> 00:17:42.760
What if I said

00:17:43.210 --> 00:17:45.350
he gave me a long, intense kiss?

00:17:53.110 --> 00:17:54.210
Let's make up.

00:18:58.890 --> 00:19:00.700
Forgive me, Sara senpai.

00:19:36.070 --> 00:19:38.010
Punish me however you want.

00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:43.400
I'm not trying to punish you.

00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:47.550
I just want to know

00:19:48.590 --> 00:19:49.790
which one of us...

00:19:51.410 --> 00:19:53.570
feels better. Him or me?

00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:08.160
Sara senpai, wait...

00:21:13.390 --> 00:21:15.030
Your lips are all swollen.

00:21:18.530 --> 00:21:20.330
That's what you get for
kissing someone else.

00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:23.270
But that was the other Fuu.

00:21:23.330 --> 00:21:24.920
And he was also Sara senpai.

00:21:25.370 --> 00:21:27.410
There's only one of me in this world.

00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:30.040
And only one of you.

00:21:30.770 --> 00:21:33.090
The Fuu in that world has that Sara senpai.

00:21:33.820 --> 00:21:35.850
This Fuu only has this Sara senpai.

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:42.600
If the kiss in the other
world was intense...

00:21:43.830 --> 00:21:44.830
then I'm not losing.

00:21:47.180 --> 00:21:48.720
Fine, I'll tell you.

00:21:51.070 --> 00:21:52.269
In the dream, it didn't
feel like I was being kissed.

00:21:52.270 --> 00:21:54.150
It felt more like I was
watching from the side.

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.040
Really?

00:21:59.280 --> 00:22:00.380
Really.

00:22:00.590 --> 00:22:01.690
Trust me.

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:04.100
Alright.

00:22:08.880 --> 00:22:09.980
Let's sleep.

00:22:10.890 --> 00:22:11.990
I'm so tired.

00:22:17.980 --> 00:22:19.120
Sara senpai.

00:22:21.150 --> 00:22:23.580
I wonder what the parallel
versions of us are doing.

00:22:28.030 --> 00:22:29.030
I'm sure

00:22:30.120 --> 00:22:31.830
they're doing exactly what we're doing.

00:22:33.290 --> 00:22:34.660
I think they're very happy, too.

00:22:58.890 --> 00:23:00.070
Good morning, Fuu.

00:23:00.880 --> 00:23:01.880
Right?

00:23:03.780 --> 00:23:05.410
That's my line.

00:23:06.720 --> 00:23:08.360
I knew you'd say it, so I beat you to it.

00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:11.630
Good morning.

00:23:21.530 --> 00:23:22.530
Good morning.

00:23:24.070 --> 00:23:25.070
Fuu.

00:23:31.870 --> 00:23:32.870
Time to get up.

00:23:36.890 --> 00:23:37.890
Give me two more minutes.

00:23:39.690 --> 00:23:40.690
Please?

00:23:41.730 --> 00:23:42.730
Hey...

00:23:47.020 --> 00:23:48.120
I'll give you five.

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:30.350
I want to play in the water.

00:25:32.500 --> 00:25:33.500
Isn't a walk enough?

00:25:35.050 --> 00:25:37.210
I want to walk and play in the water.

00:25:51.920 --> 00:25:52.920
What is it?

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:55.980
I was just thinking about
the day we first met.

00:25:56.670 --> 00:25:58.160
I mean, the very first time.

00:25:59.740 --> 00:26:01.610
You were standing at my door,

00:26:01.750 --> 00:26:03.210
soaking wet,

00:26:03.660 --> 00:26:05.920
claiming to be my lover
from a parallel world.

00:26:08.330 --> 00:26:09.600
Looking back,

00:26:10.130 --> 00:26:11.690
most people wouldn't have believed you.

00:26:13.550 --> 00:26:15.070
That's because you're special, Fuu.

00:26:17.760 --> 00:26:19.410
I'm so glad I believed you.

00:26:20.780 --> 00:26:22.340
Because of that, I'm here with you now.

00:26:37.250 --> 00:26:38.870
No matter which world it is,

00:26:39.410 --> 00:26:41.010
I hope every Fuu makes that same choice.

00:26:47.490 --> 00:26:48.820
In every world,

00:26:50.020 --> 00:26:52.840
you seem to be the light in my life.

00:26:53.990 --> 00:26:55.860
No Fuu would ever give up on Sara.

00:26:56.700 --> 00:26:57.800
That's what I believe.

00:27:00.960 --> 00:27:01.960
Then I'll pray

00:27:02.330 --> 00:27:04.350
for the world I saw in my dream last night.

00:27:05.270 --> 00:27:07.750
I'll pray that the other
Fuu finds his courage.

00:27:10.230 --> 00:27:11.730
If I were kissed like that,

00:27:12.220 --> 00:27:14.080
I would've jumped you by now.

00:27:18.470 --> 00:27:20.430
But that Fuu was just terrified.

00:27:24.360 --> 00:27:25.760
Are you happy, Sara senpai?

00:27:30.070 --> 00:27:31.270
Can't you tell?

00:27:33.530 --> 00:27:35.610
I want to hear you say it.

00:27:41.990 --> 00:27:42.990
I'm happy.

00:27:44.620 --> 00:27:46.620
I'm incredibly happy.

00:27:47.740 --> 00:27:50.490
As long as you're by
my side, that's enough.

00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:53.200
Then I...

00:27:53.650 --> 00:27:55.550
will stay by your side forever.

00:27:56.700 --> 00:27:57.700
Me too.

00:29:44.030 --> 00:29:45.320
Parallel worlds...

00:29:50.290 --> 00:29:51.490
Do you believe in them, Fuu?

00:29:55.550 --> 00:29:57.040
What if I said I didn't?

00:30:01.730 --> 00:30:03.280
Then I'd just say this.

00:30:06.900 --> 00:30:08.140
I love you.

00:30:12.610 --> 00:30:13.610
Then...

00:30:14.180 --> 00:30:15.380
I have an answer for you.

00:30:18.560 --> 00:30:20.050
I love you, Sara senpai.

00:30:44.400 --> 00:30:45.400
Knock, knock, knock.

00:30:45.810 --> 00:30:46.810
Who is it?

00:30:50.580 --> 00:30:51.580
It's dangerous.

00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:53.800
Can I stay by your side?

00:30:55.290 --> 00:30:56.710
Do you want to leave me?

00:30:57.380 --> 00:30:59.830
Don't leave me all alone.

00:31:02.110 --> 00:31:03.110
I promise.

00:31:03.980 --> 00:31:05.270
I won't leave you.

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:09.450
Have you ever wondered what we'd be like

00:31:09.480 --> 00:31:11.379
if we had never met?

00:31:11.380 --> 00:31:13.999
I probably wouldn't have made it.

00:31:14.000 --> 00:31:14.830
Neither would I.

00:31:14.831 --> 00:31:16.576
You were doing just fine
without me, weren't you?

00:31:16.600 --> 00:31:18.480
But we've already met,
so that's not an option.

00:31:49.200 --> 00:31:50.360
I finally found you.

00:31:53.450 --> 00:31:54.550
Where... am I?

00:31:56.200 --> 00:31:58.768
(This drama is a work of fiction.
Characters, organizations, and

00:31:58.792 --> 00:32:01.360
names are fictional and have
no relation to real-world entities.)